uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data

Class DumpParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data.DumpParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.xml.sax.ContentHandler, Contexed
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DiffParser, UnDumper

    public abstract class DumpParser
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.xml.sax.ContentHandler, Contexed
    A ContentHandler that parses an XML data specification created by the Dumper class The default mode is to try and reproduce the ids present in the dump. Optionally a DumpParser can generate a new id and attempt to rewrite references. Though this is only possible for entries:
    • all handled by the same parser
    • where the fields are known to be references
    • where each record only occurs once
    Author:
    spb
    See Also:
    Dumper
